  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Adequate support is required for challenging percutaneous coronary interventions (PCI). The
      &quot;TransRadial Ultra Support Technique&quot; (TRUST technique) is a new support technique that
      provides active support by deep pass of the coronary wire into the heart cavities (left
      ventricle-LV, right ventricle-RV) or aorta.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
